Kent Mitchell wrote:

&gt;One other issue is that coverage (even path coverage) follows a classic i=
nterpretation of &quot;paths&quot; being based on the structure of the code.  But for=
 an exception throwing language there is other possible &quot;paths&quot; that are tr=
iggered by behavior of the called code.  Consider:
&gt;
&gt;  public static void int parse (String s) {
&gt;
&gt;    return Integer.parseInt(s);
&gt;
&gt;  }
&gt;
&gt;Classically this has exactly one code path and gets 100% coverage if you =
pass in &quot;1234&quot; but behaviorally it has two paths because parseInt can throw=
 an exception.  So ... you really need &quot;data coverage&quot; which is a nebulous =
concept to measure at best.
